page.title: 10FURTHER NAVY USE IN GRID 05
page.content: The land in this square is owned by the Ministry of Defence and is part of The Royal Naval Armament Depot, Frater. Crossing this land is a railway line which is maintained by the Ministry of Defence for service purposes and is linked to the main railway line through Fareham. There are several piers which are used for loading armaments onto ships. This section of the coastline is restricted to Ministry of Defence use. The land is not all built up - there is a long established heronry sited in an area of deciduous woodland.
